HEADWORD: Jointly
<hw>Joint"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a joint manner; together;
unitedly; in concert; not separately.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Then <qex>jointly</qex> to the ground their knees they bow.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jointress</ent>⟦br⟧
